# Mobile Component Tests (`*.test.tsx`)

Component tests live next to the component (`ComponentName.test.tsx`) and run
under the `mobile-ui` Jest project (see `jest.config.ts`).

## Mock strategy — `moduleNameMapper` only, no `jest.mock()`

All module replacements live in `jest.config.ts`'s `rnMocks` map:

| Module | Mock file |
|---|---|
| `react-native` | `packages/mobile/__mocks__/react-native.tsx` |
| `react-native-paper` | `packages/mobile/__mocks__/react-native-paper.tsx` |
| `react-dom` | `packages/mobile/__mocks__/react-dom.tsx` |
| `react-i18next` | `packages/mobile/__mocks__/react-i18next.tsx` |
| `@react-navigation/native` | `packages/mobile/__mocks__/react-navigation-native.tsx` |
| `.*useFormatPrice$` | `packages/mobile/__mocks__/useFormatPrice.ts` |
| `.*navigation/useScreenTitle$` | `packages/mobile/__mocks__/useScreenTitle.ts` |

**Do NOT add `jest.mock()` calls to test files** — `@swc/jest` does not hoist
them reliably; `moduleNameMapper` substitutes modules before any module loads.

## Store injection

Always provide a real `RootStore` via `StoreContext.Provider`. Never use `as
unknown as RootStore` — construct a real instance with mocked API functions:

```tsx
function makeRoot(): RootStore {
  return new RootStore(
    {
      fetchCatalog: () => Promise.resolve([...]),
      sendAnalytics: () => Promise.resolve({ ok: true }),
      submitOrder: () => Promise.resolve({ orderId: "TEST" }),
    },
    { debounceMs: 0 },
  );
}
```

Call `root.dispose()` in `afterEach`.

## Rendering

`render()` and `fireEvent.*` from RNTL v14 are async — always `await` them:

```tsx
await render(<StoreContext.Provider value={root}><MyScreen /></StoreContext.Provider>);
await act(async () => { await fireEvent.press(screen.getByLabelText("increment")); });
```

## JSX runtime

`@swc/jest` is configured with `jsc.transform.react.runtime: "automatic"`.
**Do not `import React from "react"`** in test files — it's unused and will
trigger `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars`.
